---

# Good UI Design Rules

## Rule 1

Keep it simple.

Don't fill the screen with too much information.

---

## Rule 2

One primary action per screen.

Example:

Upload Screen

Only:

```text
Upload Report
```

Not:

* Upload
* Compare
* Delete
* Export
* Settings

All on one page.

---

## Rule 3

Use large buttons.

Many users will be older adults.

Buttons should be easy to tap.

---

## Rule 4

Use plain language.

Instead of:

```text
Hematological Analysis
```

Write:

```text
Blood Report
```

Simple words reduce confusion.

---

## Rule 5

Use colors carefully.

For example:

🟢 Normal

🟡 Needs Attention

🔴 Consult a Doctor

Don't rely only on color—also include text so the meaning is clear.

---

# MVP Design Philosophy

When users open the app, they should understand how to use it within 30 seconds.

If they need a tutorial, the design is probably too complicated.

